sources.description:
Feeling lost and disconnected, with no family of his own, veteran Oliver Sherman sets out to the countryside in search of the soldier who saved his life back in the war. That man, Franklin Page, has long since moved on - to a wife, two children, and a reliable job in a quiet, rural town. Upon arriving, Sherman seems at first harmless, shell of a man. But tensions rise as he reveals himself to be unstable with opaque motives. The dark and violent past of the two men begins to erode the picturesque life on Franklin's farm, and threatens the town itself.

2010.  Stars: Garret Dillahunt, Molly Parker, Donal Logue
